data.description: A classic La Veta beauty, this perfectly located two story home combines historic character with artistic southwestern charm. Inviting spaces flow between indoors and out, with thoughtful additions and updates. A gracious front porch complete with porch swing opens into the traditional central hall with tiled staircase. The living room with big sunny windows and pellet stove leads into the dining room, which opens thru french doors onto a garden dining patio with bubbling water feature. The large modern kitchen has a vaulted ceiling, island with counter seating, huge pantry and laundry room, and casual dining/seating area surrounded by windows on the back yard. One bedroom w/2 closets, a large office study and bathroom downstairs. Three bedrooms (one currently used as walkin closet) and 2nd bathroom upstairs. Situated on a fully fenced large 5 lot parcel with established landscaping, including apple and plum trees, shady back deck, vegetable garden, first class chicken coop and tool shed with power and light! The detached two-car-plus garage/shop has a new electrical panel with 240 volt for large equipment, dust collection system, insulation, drywall, wood stove and lighted attic storage. Walking distance to historic downtown Creative District, live music venue, dining and more. Call me to schedule your visit to this special gem today!
